{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"init","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"?(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"idx","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Index","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/String\/Index","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS5IndexV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"within","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"target","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"UTF8View","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS8UTF8ViewV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/String\/UTF8View"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A position in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" or one of its views."}]}],"name":"idx"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UTF8View"},{"text":" in which to find the new position.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"target"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example finds the position of a space in a string’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"utf16","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view and then converts that position to an index in the string’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"utf8"},{"type":"text","text":" view."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let cafe = \"Café 🍵\"","","let utf16Index = cafe.utf16.firstIndex(of: 32)!","let utf8Index = String.UTF8View.Index(utf16Index, within: cafe.utf8)!","","print(Array(cafe.utf8[..<utf8Index]))","\/\/ Prints \"[67, 97, 102, 195, 169]\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the position passed in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"utf16Index"},{"type":"text","text":" doesn’t have an exact"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding position in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"utf8"},{"type":"text","text":", the result of the initializer is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, because UTF-8 and UTF-16 represent high Unicode code"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"points differently, an attempt to convert the position of the trailing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"surrogate of a UTF-16 surrogate pair fails.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The next example attempts to convert the indices of the two UTF-16 code"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"points that represent the teacup emoji (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"🍵\""},{"type":"text","text":"). The index of the lead"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"surrogate is successfully converted to a position in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"utf8"},{"type":"text","text":", but the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"index of the trailing surrogate is not."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let emojiHigh = cafe.utf16.index(after: utf16Index)","print(String.UTF8View.Index(emojiHigh, within: cafe.utf8))","\/\/ Prints \"Optional(String.Index(...))\"","","let emojiLow = cafe.utf16.index(after: emojiHigh)","print(String.UTF8View.Index(emojiLow, within: cafe.utf8))","\/\/ Prints \"nil\""],"type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"id